node.text:
“A woman staying in the room in the 1940’s, that’s a big statement... And I think in 2021, it’s still a very powerful one. Women need a place at the table. Women need to stay part of the discussion, because this is how we change the world. ”

We sat down with the A.C. Bradley, the Head Writer on #Marvel's #WhatIf to discuss what happens when women stay in the room! Our interview was led by the one and only @your_pal_bucky 💪

* Marvel’s “What If…?” flips the script on the MCU, reimagining famous events from the films in unexpected ways. Featuring a voice cast that includes a host of stars reprising their roles, Marvel’s What IF is available now on Disney+. *

Sexism with @tova_leigh ☝️

"A few weeks ago I asked you to share with me examples of sexism & casual sexism in your lives. I was inundated by thousands of messages from, mainly women, who shared from their everyday lives examples of sexism and how it affects them. It’s been on my mind ever since... Sexism affects everyone, including men... But the reason I wanted to make this video is because there is a very strong link between sexism and gender inequality and I truly believe that until we break these stereotypes we’ve all been brainwashed to believe, we will struggle to achieve true equality."

Video by @tova_leigh, shared with permission. For more videos like these head over to Tova's page 🙌

node.text:
@tova_leigh: Women don't owe you pretty, James 👏

"I had to share this gem of a DM I received this morning. Pls note that I get a lot of these type of messages, especially from men who think their opinion about my body (or any other woman) matters. It doesn’t. It’s not important. It’s not relevant. And no one wants it. I’ll take it one step further - women don’t owe you pretty (like the title of the book by @florencegiven ). 

I know it’s hard to swallow but James, and others like him, can throw all the toddler tantrums they want and it still wouldn’t change the fact that women do not owe them shit. But here is why I am sharing this - you see, the obsession with women’s looks is society’s way of keeping women subordinate to men (I recommend you read @naomirwolf book The Beauty Myth). The pressure on women to spent time and money on their looks motivates sexism and slows down women’s progress in obtaining equality. You may not see the connection between the two things immediately but it’s true. In fact, the higher a woman goes, the more successful she is, the more she is perceived as a threat to the gender hierarchy, and all the more reason to keep her busy with her looks 🤷‍♀️ 

So James, I’m going take your DM as a compliment because clearly I am doing something right. And if you’ll excuse me, I’m just going to carry on prancing around in my saggy boobs, c section shelf and zero thigh gap 💪🏻 PS don’t let the door hit you on the way out 😉 

By one of our fave feminists @tova_leigh ❤
